00:12:00,070 --> 00:12:02,220
I won't be single in Heaven.

296
00:12:04,610 --> 00:12:06,200
This was the best church ever.

297
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:09,670
It was like some kind of religious experience.

298
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:11,550
Will you join us for pancakes?

299
00:12:11,980 --> 00:12:12,940
Are those new vestments?

300
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,540
They really bring out the piety.

301
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:16,670
You don't have to patronize me, Ned.

302
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:18,160
You're, y-you're right, I'm sorry.

303
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:20,180
Y-You did not do well today.

304
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:22,430
Oh, go back to patronizing.

305
00:12:22,430 --> 00:12:24,810
Maybe something about my shoes?

306
00:12:24,810 --> 00:12:28,600
Oh, look at those shoes, tied so tight with loops so even.

307
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,970
Someone knows the bunny ear technique.

308
00:12:31,130 --> 00:12:32,180
Helen tied them.

310
00:12:34,180 --> 00:12:36,320
Uh, Pastor, would you like to say grace?

311
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:37,700
Lord--

312
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:39,530
Oh, sorry, I should have been more specific.

313
00:12:39,540 --> 00:12:42,040
I meant the cool new pastor everyone likes.

314
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:43,900
You can sit down.

315
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,240
You know, I think the food is good

316
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,730
without me saying it's good.

317
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:47,830
God made it good.

318
00:12:47,830 --> 00:12:49,870
Don't get me wrong, it's nice to be thankful, but

319
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:51,720
there's no need to make everyone uncomfortable

320
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,720
by praying in front of 'em, am I right?

321
00:12:53,770 --> 00:12:56,690
Nice speech, although longer than grace.

322
00:12:57,190 --> 00:12:58,880
Oh, no bacon for me.

323
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:00,380
I'm a vegetarian.

324
00:13:00,970 --> 00:13:02,980
And, actually, a Buddhist.

325
00:13:02,980 --> 00:13:04,310
Great. I love Buddha.

326
00:13:04,310 --> 00:13:05,560
That's where I got my name.

327
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:06,540
The Bodhi Tree.

328
00:13:06,540 --> 00:13:07,670
And I don't eat meat either.

329
00:13:07,670 --> 00:13:09,160
You're a vegetarian?

330
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:11,080
- What about evolution? - Into it.

331
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,480
- Gay rights? - Love is love.

332
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,620
Dizzy or Bird?

334
00:13:13,620 --> 00:13:16,540
John Coltrane and Duke Ellington, 1962.

336
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:18,670
The only way to describe how perfect

337
00:13:18,670 --> 00:13:21,330
that jazz answer is, is with jazz.

338
00:13:29,150 --> 00:13:31,730
This brunch has turned into...

339
00:13:31,730 --> 00:13:33,870
a jazz brunch!

340
00:13:34,590 --> 00:13:35,710
I'm a believer.

341
00:13:35,710 --> 00:13:37,540
That's great, Lisa, but I actually don't think

342
00:13:37,540 --> 00:13:39,540
faith comes down to what we believe.

343
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:41,750
Well, you got to believe in this baloney.

344
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:43,250
That's how you get into Heaven.

345
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:45,470
Where maybe, just maybe, I could see

346
00:13:45,470 --> 00:13:47,330
the mother that abandoned me again.

348
00:13:49,450 --> 00:13:51,680
Yeah, sure, but I think together

349
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:54,280
we can bring Heaven here while we're still alive.

350
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,630
There's a Chinese proverb about Heaven and Hell.

351
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:59,440
They say Hell is a long table like this, full of food,

352
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:02,150
but everybody's starving because they have these long chopsticks,

353
00:14:02,150 --> 00:14:04,950
like pool cues, and they can't bring the food to their mouths.

354
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:07,340
This is the worst Year of the Ox ever.

355
00:14:07,340 --> 00:14:11,010
But in the proverb, Heaven is the exact same table, same food,

356
00:14:11,010 --> 00:14:13,620
same long chopsticks, but everybody's happy and fat

357
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:15,230
because they're feeding each other.

358
00:14:16,770 --> 00:14:19,680
Wait, wait! I can be cool, too... with humor.

359
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,810
Did you hear the one about the Greek-Jewish wedding?

360
00:14:21,810 --> 00:14:24,900
They didn't know whether to break the plates or the glasses!

362
00:14:26,580 --> 00:14:28,980
Yes, why don't you take your cultural insensitivity

363
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:32,240
back to the Spanish Inquisition you came from?

365
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,100
I've lost them.

366
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,690
You never had us.

368
00:14:39,450 --> 00:14:41,930
Timothy, the church council wants to thank you

369
00:14:41,930 --> 00:14:43,910
for your many years of...

370
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:45,370
Incompetence!

371
00:14:46,410 --> 00:14:47,650
Knock his frock off.

372
00:14:47,650 --> 00:14:50,040
We like the new guy in his tight jeans.

373
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:52,280
Do not resuscitate your career.

374
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:54,360
What are you saying? You're firing me?

375
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:57,020
- Gingo. - Please surrender your cross.

376
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,440
We don't want any trouble.

377
00:15:01,470 --> 00:15:02,610
Timothy.

378
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:07,590
Now the collar.

380
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:13,110
And any water you turned into holy water

381
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:15,260
is once again regular water.

382
00:15:15,260 --> 00:15:16,490
Nothing but tap.

383
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:28,150
Did you know Bode has 22,000 YouTube subscribers?

384
00:15:28,150 --> 00:15:29,710
Our church could go viral.

385
00:15:29,710 --> 00:15:32,200
Ugh. Close window.

386
00:15:32,210 --> 00:15:34,390
- You just subscribed. - What? No.

387
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:35,940
Now you gave him a thumbs-up.

388
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:37,460
Stop telling me what I just did.

389
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:39,580
You just gave him an eggplant emoji.

390
00:15:39,590 --> 00:15:41,960
Well, at least that can't be misconstrued.

391
00:15:41,980 --> 00:15:42,940
Wait a minute.

392
00:15:42,940 --> 00:15:45,630
The Internet can help me. Help me find something on him.

393
00:15:45,790 --> 00:15:47,160
He's clean on Google.

394
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:48,580
I'll have to try Bing.

395
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:51,360
Sorry, I was asleep.

396
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:53,460
Do you really want to use us?

397
00:15:53,530 --> 00:15:54,380
Yes.

398
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,190
Hmm. Nothing.

399
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:58,880
But I'm not licked.

400
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:00,240
Pack your bags, Helen.

401
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:02,320
We are going to Michigan.

402
00:16:06,420 --> 00:16:08,680
Reverend? We're here for a little counseling?

403
00:16:08,690 --> 00:16:09,650
Well, I'd be happy to.

404
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:11,940
But you're already with the best counselor there is.

405
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:12,650
Your partner.

406
00:16:12,650 --> 00:16:14,270
Wait. But Marge always told me

407
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:16,510
communication is bad for a marriage.

408
00:16:16,510 --> 00:16:18,250
I said it was good.

409
00:16:18,250 --> 00:16:19,420
You said what was good?

410
00:16:19,420 --> 00:16:20,670
You just have to know what it's like

411
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:22,230
to be in each other's shoes.

412
00:16:22,230 --> 00:16:24,010
Literally. Put on each other's shoes.

413
00:16:24,010 --> 00:16:24,740
Right now.

414
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:28,300
All right then.

415
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:33,130
Your shoes are so tight.

416
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:34,940
And you do so much work.

417
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:36,530
You're an angel.

418
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:38,240
And your shoes are so heavy.

419
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,870
I never realized you carried around so much.

420
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:44,230
I'm starting to see the man I fell in love with again.

421
00:16:44,230 --> 00:16:45,440
Where? Where? I'll kill him!

422
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,760
You.

423
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:49,910
I must admit, this is amazing.

424
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:52,260
But what about the fact that he sold our house?

425
00:16:52,260 --> 00:16:54,480
- Um, may I interject? - Sure.

426
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:57,400
I've seen your house. It'll never pass inspection.

427
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:59,310
- Are you sure? - Piece of crap.

428
00:16:59,470 --> 00:17:00,810
Thank you, Reverend.

430
00:17:10,090 --> 00:17:11,460
Lisa. What brings you here?

431
00:17:11,460 --> 00:17:14,120
Well, I thought it might be fun if we meditate together.

432
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:16,330
Sure. Make yourself at om.

433
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:20,440
Wow! As meditation jokes go...

434
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:24,270
That's the only meditation joke I've ever heard.

435
00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:27,700
Alexa, play Meditation Jam.

436
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:33,500
You know, science calls it consciousness,

437
00:17:33,510 --> 00:17:36,300
the mystics call it a soul, but both are just words,

438
00:17:36,300 --> 00:17:38,090
just labels, for whatever it is

439
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:40,760
that's looking out your eyes right now.

440
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:42,750
Breathe, Lisa.

443
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:29,740
Saw the button, huh?

444
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,580
I did.

447
00:18:34,060 --> 00:18:36,600
Tim, we could go to Mackinac Island.

448
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:39,270
They have the longest hotel porch in the world.

449
00:18:39,270 --> 00:18:42,170
It's always the big verandas with you, isn't it, Helen?

450
00:18:42,170 --> 00:18:43,630
You've done something to this town

451
00:18:43,630 --> 00:18:45,230
I never thought could happen.

452
00:18:45,230 --> 00:18:47,810
A full-blown religious revival.

453
00:18:50,110 --> 00:18:52,470
Yeah, let these warm your insides

454
00:18:52,470 --> 00:18:56,120
as the words of St. Paul warm your soul, there.

455
00:18:56,990 --> 00:18:58,110
Dear Ephesians--

457
00:18:58,110 --> 00:19:00,300
and I'm, of course, paraphrasing here--

458
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:03,790
believe in Christ or I'll hit your head with a baseball bat.

459
00:19:03,790 --> 00:19:05,100
I'll frickin' do it.

460
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:06,590
Amen.

461
00:19:06,610 --> 00:19:08,780
Hey, I'm-I'm not trying to change any minds.

462
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:11,120
I'm just trying to start a conversation.

463
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:14,190
We need that. This town's like a snow globe.

464
00:19:14,190 --> 00:19:17,720
It doesn't look like much till you shake it up a little.

465
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:21,530
I want redemption or else, dude.

466
00:19:21,530 --> 00:19:22,930
Or else what?

467
00:19:22,940 --> 00:19:24,980
Or Rabbi Mankiewicz will, dude.

468
00:19:24,980 --> 00:19:27,720
And I have trouble making that "Cch" Sound.

469
00:19:27,730 --> 00:19:29,990
It's either Chanukah or Hanukkah.

470
00:19:29,990 --> 00:19:31,720
Okay? Pick one of those.

473
00:19:39,660 --> 00:19:41,180
Teach a man to microfiche,

474
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:44,030
and you'll feed him dirt for a lifetime.

475
00:19:44,270 --> 00:19:47,990
Vengeance is mine, sayeth the me.

476
00:19:50,290 --> 00:19:52,790
We really should've digitized that stuff.

478
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:59,370
Oh, I hope part two is about my rescue.

